WEBVTT

00:00.367 --> 00:03.217
♪ Dancing through the snow ♪

00:03.253 --> 00:06.739
♪ in a one-horse
open sleigh ♪

00:06.824 --> 00:08.958
♪ o'er the fields
we go ♪

00:09.026 --> 00:11.077
I'm telling you, Rachel,
they know.

00:11.161 --> 00:14.230
Every day, Meachem makes some
sort of insinuating comment.

00:14.298 --> 00:15.732
"Hey, thanks
for your input, Richard.

00:15.799 --> 00:17.200
"We're gonna send you
a Christmas card

00:17.267 --> 00:18.768
when the project
gets killed."

00:18.836 --> 00:20.169
<i>"Killed"!</i>
<i>That's the word he used.</i>

00:20.237 --> 00:22.538
<i>He's trying to scare me</i>
<i>into retracting that letter.</i>

00:22.606 --> 00:24.073
Well, I can see
that you're worried.

00:24.141 --> 00:26.042
That much is clear.
I ought to be worried!

00:26.110 --> 00:27.710
The company's betting
millions on this drug.

00:27.778 --> 00:29.479
And you were right
to inform the FDA

00:29.546 --> 00:30.847
about the problems,

00:30.898 --> 00:32.515
but you did so
completely anonymously.

00:32.566 --> 00:33.916
Do you think
I'm working myself up?

00:33.984 --> 00:35.618
It has been known
to happen.

00:35.686 --> 00:37.620
Thank you for your input.
You're very welcome.

00:37.688 --> 00:39.522
This guy with his
bright lights--

00:39.573 --> 00:40.890
<i>he's speeding up.</i>

00:40.941 --> 00:43.392
♪ Jingle bells ♪
Dad?

00:43.444 --> 00:44.761
Dad, he's right
on our bumper.

00:44.828 --> 00:48.064
It's them.
It's the company.

00:49.133 --> 00:52.135
<i>Faster! Go fast!</i>
<i>Hold on!</i>

00:52.202 --> 00:54.137
<i>Hold on, honey!</i>

00:57.341 --> 00:58.441
<i>Watch out</i>
<i>for the truck!</i>

01:00.000 --> 01:06.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:09.353 --> 01:11.354
Get what we need,
then kill them.

01:15.642 --> 01:17.660
Rachel, Joel,
are you all right?

01:17.728 --> 01:18.961
I think so.
<i>Yeah. I'm fine, dad.</i>

01:19.029 --> 01:21.931
Joel?
<i>I'm fine.</i>

01:21.999 --> 01:23.933
Oh, my God.

01:24.001 --> 01:25.501
<i>They're coming.</i>

01:42.753 --> 01:44.287
Uh, Winston?

01:44.354 --> 01:46.589
Chance,
good morning.

01:46.657 --> 01:49.291
Yeah. Yeah.
Who is this guy?

01:49.343 --> 01:51.194
Him? He's just a guy
who's gonna deliver some stuff.

01:51.261 --> 01:52.428
Oh, yeah?
What stuff?

01:52.496 --> 01:54.030
You know, office stuff.

01:54.098 --> 01:56.332
Oh, like erasers,
paper clips...

01:56.400 --> 01:57.333
New fax machine?

01:57.401 --> 01:59.135
Uh, not exactly.
Right.

01:59.203 --> 02:00.837
'Cause I know what kind
of stuff he's bringing in--

02:00.904 --> 02:03.039
Christmas stuff, probably
a big tree, lights, wreath--

02:03.107 --> 02:04.841
the same stuff I tell you
not to get every year.

02:04.908 --> 02:06.242
For your information--

02:06.310 --> 02:07.693
don't even try to tell me

02:07.778 --> 02:09.579
that it's some kind of
other stuff, because it's not.

02:09.645 --> 02:11.347
I've told you before--
I don't like Christmas,

02:11.415 --> 02:12.782
never have, never will,
even though you're some kind

02:12.850 --> 02:15.451
of roly-poly Santa
in training or whatever.

02:15.519 --> 02:18.521
Did you just call me
roly-poly?

02:18.589 --> 02:21.724
Did you just hire this guy
to deliver Christmas stuff?

02:21.792 --> 02:24.894
A tree is good
for business.

02:24.962 --> 02:26.662
Clients like it.
This isn't about clients.

02:26.730 --> 02:28.865
This is about you trying
to instill in me some kind

02:28.932 --> 02:31.134
of Christmas spirit or something
ridiculous like that.

02:31.185 --> 02:32.702
You know what?
There's nothing ridiculous

02:32.770 --> 02:34.971
about having
a little holiday spirit.

02:35.038 --> 02:36.472
And you know what?
You would know that

02:36.540 --> 02:38.641
if you had
a more traditional...

02:38.709 --> 02:40.476
Childhood, happy Christmas
mornings, that kind of thing?

02:40.544 --> 02:42.411
That's right, let it out.
I know it hurts.

02:42.479 --> 02:44.147
Yeah, well, the only one
who's gonna hurt is you

02:44.214 --> 02:46.315
if a tree shows up here.

02:46.366 --> 02:48.017
Excuse me. Is, uh, one
of you Christopher Chance?

02:48.068 --> 02:50.286
Yeah, this one,
unfortunately.

02:50.354 --> 02:51.521
Oh, good.

02:51.588 --> 02:53.422
We, uh...

02:53.490 --> 02:55.691
Uh, we got a problem.

02:55.759 --> 02:58.361
So how long ago did you send
the letter to the FDA?

02:58.428 --> 02:59.762
About a month ago.

02:59.830 --> 03:01.931
It detailed
all of the research

03:01.999 --> 03:04.200
that my company,
Hoxton-Moss Pharmaceuticals,

03:04.268 --> 03:06.202
has been covering up
about a cholesterol drug

03:06.270 --> 03:07.770
that they're bringing
to the market.

03:07.838 --> 03:09.872
What did the police
have to say?

03:09.923 --> 03:11.407
Well, they said
they didn't have

03:11.475 --> 03:14.110
enough proof
and that if they did,

03:14.178 --> 03:15.411
prosecution meant
that all of us

03:15.479 --> 03:17.446
<i>are gonna have to go</i>
<i>into some sort</i>

03:17.514 --> 03:19.348
of, uh, whistle-blower's
protection program.

03:19.416 --> 03:21.117
We'd have to disappear
completely--

03:21.185 --> 03:22.685
our whole life,
basically erased.

03:22.753 --> 03:25.254
Mr. Chance,
no one will help us.

03:25.322 --> 03:27.623
<i>We've got nowhere else</i>
<i>to turn.</i>

03:27.691 --> 03:29.458
Listen, you came
to the right place.

03:29.526 --> 03:31.894
We can help you.
Mr. Winston...

03:31.962 --> 03:33.796
Is gonna ask you
a few questions,

03:33.864 --> 03:35.464
and I'll be back
in a minute.

03:38.001 --> 03:39.368
So you wanted to see me?

03:39.419 --> 03:41.754
Yes. And to think
all it took

03:41.839 --> 03:43.372
<i>was two voice mails</i>
<i>and three emails.</i>

03:43.440 --> 03:45.124
<i>Going somewhere?</i>

03:45.209 --> 03:47.093
I leave
for Uganda tonight.

03:47.177 --> 03:48.811
I'll be gone
through the new year.

03:48.879 --> 03:50.880
So if you'd be so kind as
to inform the rest of the team,

03:50.948 --> 03:52.248
I'd be most grateful.

03:52.316 --> 03:53.583
What's in Uganda?

03:53.650 --> 03:56.135
A number
of charitable organizations

03:56.220 --> 03:58.487
funded by
the Pucci Foundation.

03:58.555 --> 04:00.589
They're usually short-staffed
at this time of year,

04:00.641 --> 04:02.558
so I thought
I could be of some use.

04:02.609 --> 04:03.960
New clients?

04:04.027 --> 04:06.362
Oh. Maybe.

04:06.430 --> 04:09.632
So you're just skipping off
to Uganda over Christmas, huh?

04:09.700 --> 04:14.003
Holidays can be tough,
especially if...

04:16.240 --> 04:17.940
If...?

04:18.007 --> 04:20.543
Well, you know, if you've lost
someone close to you.

04:20.611 --> 04:24.013
It's not my favorite time
of year either.

04:27.384 --> 04:29.819
Yes, well, um--well,
I thank you for your concern,

04:29.887 --> 04:32.255
but my trip has nothing to do
with my husband's death.

04:32.322 --> 04:34.290
It has to do with preserving
what he worked on

04:34.358 --> 04:35.291
during his life.

04:35.359 --> 04:36.759
Okay.

04:36.827 --> 04:39.428
Please relay my holiday wishes
to the rest of the team,

04:39.496 --> 04:41.464
and I look forward
to continuing our work

04:41.531 --> 04:43.332
in the new year.

04:43.400 --> 04:44.967
Oh...

04:45.035 --> 04:46.636
And happy Christmas,
Mr. Chance.

04:46.703 --> 04:48.971
Oh, "merry."
We say "Merry Christmas."

04:49.039 --> 04:51.340
I know. It just sounds
a bit silly.

04:51.408 --> 04:54.076
Yeah, it does,
doesn't it?

05:00.751 --> 05:01.784
Where's she headed?

05:01.852 --> 05:02.852
Away.

05:02.920 --> 05:07.023
Yeah, well, apparently,
so are we.

05:08.725 --> 05:11.127
♪ Rhymes so loud and proud,
you hear it ♪

05:11.194 --> 05:13.529
♪ it's christmastime,
and we got the spirit ♪

05:13.597 --> 05:15.298
You got to be kidding me.

05:15.365 --> 05:18.901
♪ And that's what Christmas
is all about ♪

05:18.969 --> 05:20.703
♪ the time is now,
the place is here ♪

05:20.771 --> 05:23.839
♪ and the whole wide world
is filled with cheer ♪

05:23.907 --> 05:26.142
♪ my name's dmc
with the mic in my hand ♪

05:26.209 --> 05:27.643
Where are we?

05:27.694 --> 05:29.512
We're in hell.

05:29.579 --> 05:31.180
♪ So open your eyes,
lend us a ear ♪

05:31.231 --> 05:34.417
♪ we wanna say merry Christmas
and happy new year ♪

